---
import PortalLayout from '../layouts/PortalLayout.astro'

---

<PortalLayout
  title="Institute of Traditional Medicines"
  description="A post-reductionist institution advancing traditional pharmacological systems as sophisticated predecessors to network medicine, complex adaptive systems theory, and precision therapeutics."
>
  <div class="progress-bar-track">
    <div class="progress-bar-fill" id="reading-progress"></div>
  </div>

  <article class="institute-home">

    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         ZONE A — IDENTITY
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

    <!-- HERO — Dark full-bleed -->
    <header class="hero">
      <div class="hero-inner">
        <div class="hero-badge">Node III &mdash; Regenerative Health Ecology</div>
        <h1 class="hero-title"><span class="hero-title-top">Sohma Institute</span><br/><span class="hero-title-bottom">of Traditional Medicines</span></h1>
        <p class="hero-subtitle">A post-reductionist institution advancing traditional pharmacological systems as sophisticated predecessors to network medicine, complex adaptive systems theory, and precision therapeutics.</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- OVERVIEW — Stat strip -->
    <section id="overview" class="stat-strip">
      <div class="stat-strip-inner">
        <div class="stat-item">
          <div class="stat-numeral">III</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Node Position</div>
          <p class="stat-desc">Third arm of the Regenerative Health Ecology. Sits between clinical application and public dissemination.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-divider"></div>
        <div class="stat-item">
          <div class="stat-numeral">RTO</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Institutional Class</div>
          <p class="stat-desc">Registered Training Organisation with articulation to university postgraduate programs.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="stat-divider"></div>
        <div class="stat-item">
          <div class="stat-numeral">QLD</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Jurisdictional Anchor</div>
          <p class="stat-desc">Headquartered in Cairns. Tropical and Indigenous medicine specialisations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- EPISTEMOLOGY — Tinted contrast band -->
    <section id="epistemology" class="epist-band">
      <div class="epist-inner">
        <div class="section-label">Foundational Intellectual Position</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">The Post-Reductionist Correction</h2>

        <p class="epist-lead">The dominant framing positions traditional medicines as "complementary" or "alternative" to evidence-based practice. This framing is intellectually bankrupt. The Institute inverts it.</p>

        <div class="epist-panels">
          <div class="epist-panel reject">
            <div class="epist-icon">
              <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>What We Reject</h3>
            <div class="epist-items">
              <div class="epist-item struck"><span>CAM framing</span></div>
              <div class="epist-item struck"><span>Integrative apologetics</span></div>
              <div class="epist-item struck"><span>Vitalism without mechanism</span></div>
            </div>
            <p>The "complementary and alternative" paradigm forces traditional systems into a subordinate epistemological position where they must prove themselves against criteria designed for isolated molecular entities.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="epist-panel advance">
            <div class="epist-icon">
              <svg width="28" height="28" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3>What We Advance</h3>
            <div class="epist-items">
              <div class="epist-item lit"><span>Network pharmacology</span></div>
              <div class="epist-item lit"><span>Systems biology</span></div>
              <div class="epist-item lit"><span>Complexity therapeutics</span></div>
            </div>
            <p>Traditional systems as sophisticated predecessors to network medicine. Ayurveda, TCM, Unani, Kampo, and Indigenous pharmacopoeia as mature therapeutic architectures.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="convergence-callout">
          <div class="convergence-title">The Convergence Thesis</div>
          <div class="convergence-cols">
            <div>
              <div class="convergence-label">Traditional Logic</div>
              <p>Constitutional classification &rarr; personalised formula &rarr; multi-constituent preparation &rarr; whole-system response assessment over time</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="convergence-label">Modern Equivalent</div>
              <p>Pharmacogenomic profiling &rarr; precision therapeutics &rarr; polypharmacology &rarr; systems biology outcome measurement via multi-omics</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <div class="convergence-label">Institute Position</div>
              <p>These are not analogies. They are convergent descriptions of the same therapeutic reality, arrived at through different investigative methodologies.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
         ZONE B — STRUCTURE
         ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

    <!-- DIVISIONS — Dark horizontal grid -->
    <section id="divisions" class="divisions-dark">
      <div class="divisions-inner">
        <div class="section-label light">Five Academic Divisions</div>
        <h2 class="section-title light">Institute Divisions</h2>
        <p class="divisions-intro">Each division operates as a semi-autonomous academic unit with its own research agenda, credentialing pathway, and clinical translation pipeline.</p>

        <div class="divisions-grid">
          <div class="division-col" data-accent="terracotta">
            <div class="division-dot"></div>
            <span class="division-num">I</span>
            <h3>Complex Herbal Medicines</h3>
            <p>Multi-constituent botanical therapeutics, phytochemical synergy, traditional pharmacopoeia systems, and clinical herbal prescribing.</p>
            <div class="division-pills">
              <span>Phytopharmacology</span>
              <span>Ethnobotany</span>
              <span>Pharmacognosy</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="division-col" data-accent="warm">
            <div class="division-dot"></div>
            <span class="division-num">II</span>
            <h3>Emergent & Entheogenic Modalities</h3>
            <p>Cannabis medicine, psilocybin-assisted therapy, psychedelic integration, and novel consciousness-based therapeutic frameworks.</p>
            <div class="division-pills">
              <span>Cannabis Therapeutics</span>
              <span>Psychedelic Therapy</span>
              <span>Harm Reduction</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="division-col" data-accent="blue">
            <div class="division-dot"></div>
            <span class="division-num">III</span>
            <h3>Systems & Functional Medicine</h3>
            <p>Systems biology approaches to chronic complex illness, functional diagnostics, metabolomic and genomic interpretation.</p>
            <div class="division-pills">
              <span>Functional Diagnostics</span>
              <span>Metabolomics</span>
              <span>Genomics</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="division-col" data-accent="teal">
            <div class="division-dot"></div>
            <span class="division-num">IV</span>
            <h3>Environmental & Nutritional Medicine</h3>
            <p>Toxicant exposure assessment, environmental determinants, clinical nutrition, microbiome therapeutics.</p>
            <div class="division-pills">
              <span>Clinical Nutrition</span>
              <span>Toxicology</span>
              <span>Microbiome</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="division-col" data-accent="purple">
            <div class="division-dot"></div>
            <span class="division-num">V</span>
            <h3>Lifestyle & Relational Medicine</h3>
            <p>Somatic therapy, contemplative practice, movement medicine, sleep architecture, and relational health.</p>
            <div class="division-pills">
              <span>Somatic Therapy</span>
              <span>Movement Medicine</span>
              <span>Sleep Science</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>


    <!-- PUBLISHING — Compact list -->
    <section id="publishing" class="publishing-section">
      <div class="section-label">Knowledge Dissemination</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Publishing Arm</h2>

      <div class="publishing-list">
        <div class="publishing-item">
          <span class="publishing-tag green">Flagship</span>
          <div class="publishing-content">
            <h3>Journal of Traditional & Network Medicine</h3>
            <p>Peer-reviewed, open-access. Original research, systematic reviews, case series. Editorial commitment to whole-systems research design. Indexed target: DOAJ, Scopus within 3 years.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="publishing-item">
          <span class="publishing-tag warm">Clinical Resource</span>
          <div class="publishing-content">
            <h3>Protocol Monograph Series</h3>
            <p>Detailed clinical protocol documents for network practitioners. Full evidence summary, prescribing guidelines, outcome measures, contraindications. Living documents updated as registry data accumulates.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="publishing-item">
          <span class="publishing-tag terracotta">Public Scholarship</span>
          <div class="publishing-content">
            <h3>Institute Working Papers</h3>
            <p>Pre-publication working papers on emerging research, policy analysis, and theoretical contributions. Rapid publication cycle for timely commentary on regulatory developments.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="publishing-item">
          <span class="publishing-tag blue">Education</span>
          <div class="publishing-content">
            <h3>Textbook Series</h3>
            <p>Division-specific textbooks authored by Institute faculty. Written for the Institute's pedagogical framework. Incorporate the convergence thesis throughout.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </article>
</PortalLayout>

<style>
  /* ═══════════ GLOBAL RESETS ═══════════ */
  .institute-home {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    padding: 0;
  }
  .institute-home p { line-height: 1.8; margin: 0 0 1rem; }
  .institute-home p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
  .institute-home h2, .institute-home h3 { margin: 0; }

  /* Section labels (reused across zones) */
  .section-label {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .section-label::after {
    content: '';
    flex: 1;
    height: 1px;
    background: var(--accent-line);
  }
  .section-label.light { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); }
  .section-label.light::after { background: rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }

  .section-title {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 2.25rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    line-height: 1.15;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .section-title.light { color: var(--text-on-dark); }

  .section-intro {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--text-body-65);
    line-height: 1.85;
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  /* ═══════════ PROGRESS BAR ═══════════ */
  .progress-bar-track { position: sticky; top: 0; z-index: 10; height: 3px; background: var(--bg-card); }
  .progress-bar-fill { height: 100%; width: 0; background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--accent-dark), var(--accent)); transition: width 0.1s; }


  /* ═══════════ HERO ═══════════ */
  .hero {
    margin-left: -40px;
    margin-right: -40px;
    padding: 5rem 40px 3.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-base);
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }
  .hero::before {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    bottom: 0;
    background: none;
    pointer-events: none;
  }
  .hero::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 0;
    left: 0;
    right: 0;
    height: 3px;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, transparent, var(--accent-border-20) 30%, var(--accent-soft-20) 70%, transparent);
  }
  .hero-inner { position: relative; z-index: 1; max-width: 700px; }
  .hero-badge {
    display: inline-block;
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-border-25);
    padding: 5px 14px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .hero-title {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    line-height: 1.1;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }
  .hero-title-top {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.75rem);
  }
  .hero-title-bottom {
    font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5.5vw, 3.75rem);
  }
  .institute-home .hero-subtitle {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2vw, 1.25rem);
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-body-55);
    line-height: 1.4;
    margin: 0 0 2.5rem;
    max-width: 600px;
  }
  /* ═══════════ STAT STRIP ═══════════ */
  .stat-strip {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }
  .stat-strip-inner {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    justify-content: center;
    gap: 0;
  }
  .stat-item {
    flex: 1;
    text-align: center;
    padding: 0 2rem;
  }
  .stat-divider {
    width: 1px;
    height: 80px;
    background: var(--border-medium);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    align-self: center;
  }
  .stat-numeral {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .stat-label {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .stat-desc {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-body-55);
    line-height: 1.6;
    max-width: 240px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    text-align: center;
  }


  /* ═══════════ EPISTEMOLOGY BAND ═══════════ */
  .epist-band {
    margin-left: -40px;
    margin-right: -40px;
    padding: 4rem 80px;
    background: var(--text-on-dark);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--bg-card);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bg-card);
  }
  .epist-inner { max-width: 100%; }
  .epist-lead {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.35;
    max-width: 640px;
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }
  .epist-panels {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .epist-panel {
    padding: 2.25rem 2rem;
    position: relative;
  }
  .epist-panel.reject {
    background: var(--accent-hover-bg);
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-soft-10);
  }
  .epist-panel.advance {
    background: rgba(104,124,87,0.05);
    border-radius: 6px;
    border: 1px solid rgba(104,124,87,0.12);
  }
  .epist-icon {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .epist-panel.reject .epist-icon { color: var(--accent-soft-60); }
  .epist-panel.advance .epist-icon { color: var(--accent-green); }
  .epist-panel h3 {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .epist-panel.reject h3 { color: var(--accent-soft-75); }
  .epist-panel.advance h3 { color: var(--accent-green); }
  .epist-panel p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  /* Reject items — struck through */
  .epist-items {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.625rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .epist-item {
    position: relative;
    padding: 8px 14px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .epist-item span {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .epist-item.struck {
    background: var(--accent-hover-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--accent-soft-08);
  }
  .epist-item.struck span {
    color: var(--accent-text-80);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  /* Advance items — glowing / highlighted */
  .epist-item.lit {
    background: rgba(104,124,87,0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(104,124,87,0.18);
    box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(104,124,87,0.06);
  }
  .epist-item.lit span {
    color: var(--accent-green-deep);
  }

  /* Convergence callout */
  .convergence-callout {
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }
  .convergence-title {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }
  .convergence-cols {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
  .convergence-label {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 0.625rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent-dark);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
  .convergence-cols p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }


  /* ═══════════ DIVISIONS DARK BAND ═══════════ */
  .divisions-dark {
    margin-left: -40px;
    margin-right: -40px;
    padding: 4.5rem 40px;
    background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-dark-start) 0%, var(--bg-dark-end) 100%);
  }
  .divisions-inner { max-width: 100%; }
  .divisions-intro {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: rgba(240,235,229,0.4);
    line-height: 1.75;
    max-width: 620px;
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }
  .divisions-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
  }
  .division-col {
    padding: 1.75rem 1.25rem;
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.02);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.04);
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background 0.25s, border-color 0.25s;
  }
  .division-col:hover {
    background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
    border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);
  }
  .division-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  [data-accent="terracotta"] .division-dot { background: var(--accent-dark); }
  [data-accent="warm"] .division-dot { background: var(--chart-warm); }
  [data-accent="blue"] .division-dot { background: var(--chart-blue); }
  [data-accent="teal"] .division-dot { background: var(--chart-teal); }
  [data-accent="purple"] .division-dot { background: var(--chart-purple); }

  .division-num {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    color: rgba(240,235,229,0.2);
    line-height: 1;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .division-col h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-on-dark);
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .division-col p {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: rgba(240,235,229,0.4);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }
  .division-pills {
    display: flex;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }
  .division-pills span {
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    color: rgba(240,235,229,0.3);
    border: 1px solid rgba(240,235,229,0.08);
    border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 2px 6px;
  }


  /* ═══════════ PUBLISHING LIST ═══════════ */
  .publishing-section {
    padding: 3rem 0 2rem;
  }
  .publishing-list {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }
  .publishing-item {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bg-card);
    transition: background 0.15s;
  }
  .publishing-item:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .publishing-item:hover { background: var(--bg-card); }

  .publishing-tag {
    font-family: 'Manrope', sans-serif;
    font-size: 0.5625rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 2px;
    white-space: nowrap;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }
  .publishing-tag.green { color: var(--accent-green); background: rgba(104,124,87,0.08); }
  .publishing-tag.warm { color: var(--chart-warm); background: var(--chart-warm-bg); }
  .publishing-tag.terracotta { color: var(--accent-dark); background: var(--accent-active-bg); }
  .publishing-tag.blue { color: var(--chart-blue); background: var(--chart-blue-bg); }

  .publishing-content h3 {
    font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .publishing-content p {
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--text-body-60);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }


  /* ═══════════ RESPONSIVE ═══════════ */
  @media (max-width: 1024px) {
    .divisions-grid { grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .hero { padding: 3.5rem 40px 2.5rem; }
    .hero-title { font-size: 2.25rem; }

